TITLE: Chef José Andrés and his daughters go on a Spanish food tour in new TV show
SUMMARY: In “José Andrés and Family in Spain” on Discovery+, the chef embarks on a culinary journey in his homeland alongside his three American-raised daughters

TITLE: In Mexico, legal struggle to free women jailed for abortion continues
SUMMARY: Even though Mexico's Supreme Court decriminalized abortion last year, hundreds of women remain in prison under outdated anti-abortion state laws, advocates said

TITLE: U.S. to require negative Covid test for travelers from China as virus spreads
SUMMARY: The new policy comes amid a surge in Covid cases in China and as fears of a new variant emerge

TITLE: Francis calls for prayers for former Pope Benedict’s health
SUMMARY: Pope Francis revealed his predecessor, Benedict XVI, is very sick in a call for prayers during his general audience. The 95-year-old’s condition worsened due to his age, the Vatican says

TITLE: Massive Russian missile barrage pummels cities across Ukraine
SUMMARY: Major cities were left without power as Russia launched its biggest wave of strikes in recent weeks

TITLE: Novak Djokovic says there are no hard feelings over deportation as he returns for Australian Open
SUMMARY: Djokovic has won the Australian Open a record nine times, including the last three times he played. Rafael Nadal won the 2022 title in Djokovic’s absence

TITLE: Massive fire at Cambodia hotel casino kills at least 19
SUMMARY: Videos posted on social media showed people falling from a roof after they were trapped by the fire at the Grand Diamond City casino and hotel in the town of Poipet

TITLE: American tourists stranded in Machu Picchu as deadly unrest sweeps Peru
SUMMARY: Violent protests erupted following the ousting and detention of President Pedro Castillo, who had sought to dissolve Parliament in a last-minute power grab

TITLE: Argentina wins World Cup on penalty kicks over France: Live updates
SUMMARY: Sunday's final capped a month of sporting drama and geopolitical controversy in Qatar

TITLE: Pope Francis wrote resignation note after 2013 election in case of health impediment
SUMMARY: “I have already signed my renunciation,” Francis revealed in an interview published Sunday with Spanish newspaper ABC, noting that he did so early in the papacy
